-- HSBC Holdings Said to Hire Sunil Sanghai From Goldman Sachs for India Unit
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-06-22T12:17:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/hsbc-holdings-said-to-hire-sunil-sanghai-from-goldman-sachs-for-india-unit.html

          
          
             HSBC Holdings Plc  hired Goldman
Sachs Group Inc.’s Managing Director  Sunil Sanghai , according to
two people familiar with the matter.  
 Sanghai, who was co-head of investment banking at Goldman
Sachs in Mumbai, quit his position yesterday, one of the people
said, declining to be identified before a public announcement.  
 Edward Naylor , a Hong Kong-based spokesman for Goldman
Sachs, and  Malini Thadani , a Mumbai-based spokeswoman for HSBC,
declined to comment. Sanghai couldn’t immediately be reached at
his Goldman Sachs office.  
 Sanghai may be named managing director for global banking-
corporate and investment banking in India by HSBC, the  Economic
Times  reported earlier today.  
